reviewText: Thanks to University of Penn for giving me the opportunity to learn from highly skilled trainers to teach me Excel for Beginners: Pivot Tables. The course is very good and is for people who are looking to develop their career in Micorsoft Excel. Taking this course has been a added advantage to my career goals.
Like the instructor, keep you engaged with Excel, Not a fast-paced class, wish there was a key terms/icon legend to refer to

Valuable course and good instructor, but technical issues with reaching, editing and manipulating the file with Excel Online, and difficulty of both following the instructor and working on your file at the same time was difficult. If you have two monitors, or can use the laptop for one and your monitor for the other, then separate screens should make it easy.The content was good and valuable, but I felt like two hours significantly underestimates the time I devoted to it, given that I had to go back and forth and do those things at the same time as the instructor. I would say I spent 5-6 hours in total. The course was loaded, applying all you learn sometimes takes time.
it's very helpful and I enjoyed with it , Now i enable to create. charts and dashboard
Instructor speaks clearly and at a very good pace to understand. His examples and sample documents and various pivot tables and charts were great.
Excellent tutorial including guided trainer examples.
